Their strategy worked very well and pushed the company to new heights. Cozmo's line of mountain bikes, sports bikes, road bikes and regular city bikes were quite popular with consumers across North America and Europe. 

Soon, Cozmo expanded to Asia by setting up manufacturing centers in China and Indonesia. In North America and Europe, its products were very popular with sports enthusiasts. Its bikes were priced in the $200-$300 range. In India and other Asian countries, it was better known for its durable, utility bikes, that were priced in the $50-$100 range. 